The National Association of Resident Doctors of Nigeria (NARD) has condemned alleged harassment of its members by the Joint Health Sector Union (JOHESU) during the latterâ€™s ongoing industrial action. NARD said members of JOHESU, who are presently on an indefinite strike, were harassing doctors in hospitals in the country under the guise of implementing the industrial action. In an interview with Daily Trust yesterday, First Vice President of the association, Dr Ganiyu Olanipekun Ahmed said while JOHESU has the right to agitate for improved welfare, it is important for its members to conduct themselves with civility in the workplace and in accordance with labour laws. He said following the strike, JOHESU members have become increasingly aggressive towards other health professional particularly doctors, who are not on strike, adding that JOHESU members at the Nnamdi Azikiwe Teaching Hospital, Awka beat up a resident The National Chairman of JOHESU, Biobelemoye Josiah, did not respond to calls and text messages to him for his response to the allegation as at press time.